Braves Beat Nationals 2-0 on Opening Day of Major League Baseball Season

-- B y   E r i k   M a t u s z e w s k i
-- 
2011-03-31T19:50:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-31/braves-beat-nationals-2-0-on-opening-day-of-major-league-baseball-season.html
The  Atlanta Braves  beat the
Washington Nationals 2-0 on Major League Baseball’s Opening Day
as Jason Heyward hit the first home run of the season.  Heyward hit a solo homer in the second inning at Nationals
Park in Washington while Braves starting pitcher Derek Lowe and
four relievers combined on a five-hit shutout.  There are six games scheduled today as the major league
season begins on a Thursday for the first time in 35 years. The
 New York Yankees  are hosting the Detroit Tigers at Yankee
Stadium in the first of three nationally televised games on Walt
Disney Co.’s ESPN.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Erik Matuszewski in New York at 
 matuszewski@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Sillup at   msillup@bloomberg.net  